# Solar Navigator — Cursor Rules

## Project Identity
This is an **AI agent coding experiment**. Every feature is co-created with AI coding agents;
the human author's role is to direct and review, not write code manually. Favour clean,
idiomatic Rust that future agents can extend with minimal context.

## Tech Stack
- **Rust** (2024 edition) + **Bevy 0.18.1** (ECS game engine)
- **bevy_egui** for the side panel UI
- **rust-spice** (optional `spice` feature) wrapping NAIF CSPICE for ephemerides
- **reqwest** for NASA JPL Horizons HTTP queries
- **wgpu v27** / Metal (macOS) rendering backend

## Module Layout
```
src/
  main.rs          — calls app::run()
  ephemeris.rs     — SpiceEphemeris + Horizons HTTP client (no Bevy)
  app/
    mod.rs         — Bevy App construction; registers all systems and resources
    types.rs       — every Resource, Component, and the BODIES constant array
    setup.rs       — Startup systems: scene spawn, texture loading, Horizons sync
    simulation.rs  — Update systems: keyboard input, time advance, body positions
    camera.rs      — Update systems: orbit camera, jump/fly-to, tracking
    render.rs      — Update systems: lighting, visibility, window title
    materials.rs   — PlanetAtmosphereMaterial (custom WGSL shader)
    ui.rs          — egui side panel
    util.rs        — asset resolution, image helpers, format_simulation_speed
```

## Key Conventions
- All `app/` types are `pub(super)` — nothing leaks out of the module.
- Bevy resources are defined in `types.rs`; systems live in the module that owns them.
- `BODIES` in `types.rs` is the canonical static array of all 14 rendered bodies.
- Both feature variants must compile and pass clippy/tests:
  - `cargo check --all-targets`
  - `cargo check --all-targets --no-default-features`
- `clippy -D warnings` is enforced in CI — no `#[allow]` without a comment explaining why.

## Coordinate System
SPICE `ECLIPJ2000` (Z = ecliptic north) is remapped to Bevy Y-up:
```
scene_x =  spice_x * AU_TO_SCENE_UNITS
scene_y =  spice_z * AU_TO_SCENE_UNITS   ← SPICE Z → Bevy Y
scene_z = -spice_y * AU_TO_SCENE_UNITS   ← negated to preserve right-handedness
```

## Build Commands
```bash
cargo run --release --no-default-features   # portable, always works
cargo run --release                         # SPICE build (needs vendor/cspice)
cargo fmt --check
cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings
cargo test --all-targets
```

## Adding a Body
1. Add a `BodySpec` entry to `BODIES` in `types.rs`.
2. Add a `horizons_command_for_target` mapping in `ephemeris.rs`.
3. Mark it in `spice_supports_target` if SPICE kernels cover it.
